commit.message:
Add support for numpy.vectorize

This all relies on existing logic around numpy_expr, so no big deal in
terms of extra features to add.

This also paves the way for #2141  as we now "just" need to write a generic
converted for `numpy::vectorized<F>`.

Support numpy.argsort kind keyword argument

Reusing the infrastructure from numpy.ndarray.sort

Fix #2172

Allow taking the real/imag part of a numpy_iexpr

This does not create a copy, but man how fragile is this?

Fix #2173

Add missing descriptor for omp.set_num_threads

Fix #2174
Fix constant folding in aug assign

Add missing baseid() method for sliced list

Fix #2178

Provide --trace-allocations switch

When turned on, Pythran instrument the generated code so that it dumps
line number information about python statements that lead to memory allocation.

Centralize all pythran-managed allocation in one place

This should make it easier to instrument allocations.

As a side effect slightly improve some string manipulation.

Fix numpy bool type conversion, and properly support np.bool_

Fix #2175

Support empty PYTHRANRC

This should help reproducible builds.

Related to #2170
Read the docs update - .readthedocs.yaml
Remove swap files

0.15.0 - ibil

falla ibil zo er c'harr a wigour da genta
When failing to find pythran-openblas, default to none

Remove xsimd and boost from git ignore file

This is now their expected location

Avoid redefining `NPY_NO_DEPRECATED_API` if already defined by user

This caused macro redefined warnings in SciPy when globally setting
this macro on all build targets that have a numpy dependency.

Fix tuple + indexable_container combiner

The order of the combination matters, and it wasn't respected.

Fix #2160

Upgrade xsimd to a48ab430d4b84ecd5449180ee1c6d2eed67c4191

Fix #2164

Move setup configuration to pyproject.toml

Related to https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/19670

Correctly handle overlapping detection between gexpr and vexpr

Fix #2158

Detect situation where functions are called as methods

Fix #2156
Add support for clear for lists

Avoid extra allocation when evaluation complex gexpr

Improve the simple runtime alias analysis to prevent some memory copies,
based on the origin of each subexpression.
Update icc github action

Support Python 3.12

This adds a dependency on setuptools and get rids of references to
numpy.distutils and (part of) distutils.

Fix #2148
Use a requirement file for test requirements

Remove pytest.mark.module usage

I never use it and we get some warnings about it.
0.14.0 - falzig

Do not override numpy.random spec information as they are unstable

We where already turning off the warning, so actually do what this silencing
suggests.

CI updates: add Python 3.11, and other minor maintenance

- Spread out jobs more across Python versions
- Update to the latest setup-python actions
